This paper deals with computational complexity theory and quantum computing, which are both covered by the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.QI (Quantum Physics) sub-categories. The paper also involves the study of the polynomial hierarchy, which falls under the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses the Ellipsoid Method, which is a technique in optimization and falls under the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category.
